00:48.174 --> 00:50.224
PETE: "This is...

00:50.385 --> 00:55.635
"the story of a puppy.

00:55.807 --> 00:59.387
"His name is...

00:59.561 --> 01:01.521
"El-i..."

01:01.688 --> 01:03.768
- Elliot.
- "Elliot.

01:03.940 --> 01:06.360
"His name is Elliot."

01:06.526 --> 01:07.736
You got it.

01:07.902 --> 01:10.912
"He is going on an...

01:11.072 --> 01:13.872
"adventure..."

01:14.033 --> 01:15.953
- An adventure.
- What's that?

01:16.161 --> 01:17.451
An adventure?

01:17.537 --> 01:18.977
You don't know what an adventure is?

01:19.497 --> 01:20.867
What we're on right now.

01:21.040 --> 01:22.920
Out here in the wild,

01:23.001 --> 01:25.631
not another soul in sight
for hundreds of miles...

01:25.837 --> 01:27.667
with just the stars to guide us.

01:27.839 --> 01:29.719
Is it scary?

01:30.467 --> 01:32.427
That's the other thing about adventures.

01:32.594 --> 01:34.264
You gotta be brave.

01:34.429 --> 01:35.889
Are you brave?

01:36.055 --> 01:37.345
Of course you are.

01:38.099 --> 01:42.399
I think you are the bravest boy
I've ever met.

01:43.021 --> 01:44.021
(CHUCKLES)

01:45.482 --> 01:46.482
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:55.283 --> 01:56.623
(CAR CRASHING)

02:08.420 --> 02:09.961
(PETE CRYING)

02:11.633 --> 02:12.883
PETE: Momma.

02:27.315 --> 02:28.595
(ANIMAL CALLING IN THE DISTANCE)

02:36.324 --> 02:37.334
(RUSTLING)

02:42.372 --> 02:43.712
(ANIMALS HOWLING)

02:45.166 --> 02:46.626
(ANIMALS GROWLING)

02:57.846 --> 02:58.846
(PANTING)

03:14.696 --> 03:17.026
- (WOLVES GROWLING AND HOWLING)
- (RUSTLING)

03:35.216 --> 03:36.926
- (LOUD THUDDING)
- (YELPS)

03:39.762 --> 03:41.322
- (BRANCHES CRACKING)
- (WOLVES YELPING)

04:15.006 --> 04:16.966
Are you gonna eat me?

04:17.382 --> 04:18.382
(EXCLAIMS)

04:25.433 --> 04:26.433
(SNIFFLES)

04:29.520 --> 04:31.310
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

04:48.122 --> 04:49.122
(EXHALES)

05:10.937 --> 05:12.647
(MAKING GUTTURAL NOISES)

06:15.793 --> 06:17.003
(MUSIC PLAYING)

06:22.258 --> 06:23.258
(HAMMERING)

06:24.635 --> 06:29.215
<i>Go North, go North
With wings on your feet</i>

06:30.183 --> 06:34.603
<i>Go North with the wind
Where the three rivers meet</i>

06:35.480 --> 06:40.360
<i>There's a clearing of sorts
In the circle of trees</i>

06:40.777 --> 06:41.777
(INAUDIBLE)

06:42.570 --> 06:44.650
<i>Where the wild constellations shine
One two and three</i>

06:46.491 --> 06:51.161
<i>Look all around you and see</i>

06:51.913 --> 06:56.633
<i>Deep in the forest there dragons will be</i>

06:59.879 --> 07:01.273
MEACHAM: <i>As long as
people have been</i>

07:01.297 --> 07:02.797
<i>going into these woods...</i>

07:02.965 --> 07:05.675
<i>there have been stories
about the Millhaven dragon.</i>

07:07.178 --> 07:08.928
<i>How does that song go again?</i>

07:09.013 --> 07:10.353
<i>They come from the North, right?</i>

07:10.515 --> 07:11.885
<i>Way up there in the mountains</i>

07:11.974 --> 07:13.814
<i>where few people have ever been.</i>

07:13.976 --> 07:15.346
<i>But sometimes,</i>

07:15.478 --> 07:17.648
<i>a dragon gets lost from its family...</i>

07:17.814 --> 07:20.824
<i>and winds up very, very far from home.</i>

07:20.983 --> 07:24.573
<i>They say it lives in these very woods.</i>

07:24.737 --> 07:27.197
<i>That you can hear its roar at night.</i>

07:27.657 --> 07:32.157
<i>They say this, they say that,
but, as far as I know...</i>

07:32.328 --> 07:36.328
<i>not one soul has ever
actually seen this dragon.</i>

07:36.499 --> 07:37.959
- Except me.
- (CHILDREN GASP)

07:38.042 --> 07:39.592
You saw a dragon?

07:39.752 --> 07:41.002
I sure did.

07:41.838 --> 07:43.088
Ooh.

07:43.172 --> 07:44.422
I sure did.

07:45.216 --> 07:46.216
What'd it look like?

07:46.384 --> 07:47.434
Well, it was green.

07:47.844 --> 07:49.104
Green all over.

07:49.178 --> 07:51.138
- Except for his eyes.
- JENNY: My favorite color!

07:52.431 --> 07:54.771
His eyes were red. Like hellfire.

07:55.685 --> 07:57.185
Before I could even blink...

07:57.353 --> 08:01.773
it rears back its head,
opens its mighty jaw...

08:01.941 --> 08:02.941
and shoots out...

08:03.025 --> 08:04.025
(CHILDREN GASP)

08:05.236 --> 08:06.276
(CHILDREN CHUCKLING)

08:06.362 --> 08:07.782
So, I wasn't gonna waste my breath.

08:07.947 --> 08:10.027
I rolled out the way,
scrambled to my feet...

08:10.199 --> 08:11.677
ready for the fight that was gonna come.

08:11.701 --> 08:13.201
But as I raised my rifle...

08:13.369 --> 08:16.039
the dragon comes at me
with one swipe of its claw...

08:16.205 --> 08:17.599
knocks the gun right out of my hands.

08:17.623 --> 08:18.623
Now, what?

08:18.791 --> 08:20.391
Things are really not looking good here.

08:21.377 --> 08:24.207
But I wasn't gonna be done. Not yet.

08:24.922 --> 08:26.882
I just took out my pocket knife...

08:27.049 --> 08:29.549
And as the dragon set upon me...

08:30.428 --> 08:31.428
(CHILDREN GASP)

08:32.263 --> 08:33.263
I drove it home.

08:33.722 --> 08:34.722
Whoa!

08:34.890 --> 08:36.561
GRACE: Scaring the kids again, Dad?

08:36.726 --> 08:38.806
No, no, no. I was just
giving them a leg up...

08:38.977 --> 08:40.607
on what's out there in those woods.

08:41.313 --> 08:43.984
Well, I'm out in those woods every day...

08:44.150 --> 08:46.650
and while I have seen
bears and bobcats...

08:46.819 --> 08:49.819
and just about every type
of bird you can imagine.

08:50.489 --> 08:53.489
I have never seen a dragon.

08:54.952 --> 08:56.388
Just because you don't see something,

08:56.412 --> 08:57.582
doesn't mean it's not there.

08:57.747 --> 08:59.667
And just because you say it's true,

08:59.749 --> 09:00.919
doesn't mean it is.

09:01.083 --> 09:02.383
- (CHUCKLES)
- (CHILDREN EXCLAIM)

09:02.460 --> 09:04.750
But, I'm headed out there right now.

09:04.921 --> 09:06.551
I'll let you all know if I see anything

09:06.631 --> 09:09.091
big and green and breathing fire.

09:10.593 --> 09:12.603
Mr. MEACHAM, I believe you.

09:12.762 --> 09:15.262
Well, I'm glad you do.
See, my daughter...

09:15.848 --> 09:17.228
<i>she knows a thing or two</i>

09:17.308 --> 09:19.598
<i>but only if it's staring
at her in the face.</i>

09:19.769 --> 09:21.099
<i>If you go through life</i>

09:21.187 --> 09:22.867
<i>only seeing what's
right in front of you...</i>

09:22.939 --> 09:24.479
you're gonna miss out on a whole lot.

09:25.608 --> 09:28.278
<i>See, and that's where
you guys have the upper hand.</i>

09:29.111 --> 09:30.451
<i>Because mark my words...</i>

09:30.613 --> 09:32.663
that dragon is still out there.

09:33.115 --> 09:34.115
(GROWLING)

09:34.200 --> 09:36.160
<i>And if you were to go
out there to those woods...</i>

09:37.119 --> 09:38.159
where no one ever goes...

09:39.622 --> 09:40.672
then you might find him.

09:43.459 --> 09:46.499
Unless, he found you first.

09:47.296 --> 09:48.296
(ROARING)

10:05.481 --> 10:06.481
Gotcha!

10:08.150 --> 10:09.740
(BEAR GRUNTING)

10:21.497 --> 10:22.497
(EXHALES)

10:22.581 --> 10:23.921
(ROARING)

10:30.214 --> 10:32.264
(SCREAMING)

10:41.684 --> 10:42.694
(CHUCKLES)

10:45.354 --> 10:46.364
Hey, Elliot!

10:46.689 --> 10:48.439
(MAKING GUTTURAL NOISES)

11:25.561 --> 11:26.771
What was that for?

11:29.398 --> 11:30.398
Come on, Elliot!

11:38.115 --> 11:39.115
(GRUNTS)

11:52.254 --> 11:53.264
Elliot?

11:55.091 --> 11:56.091
- (SOFT GRUNT)
- (GASPS)

12:03.933 --> 12:04.933
(CHUCKLES)

12:11.190 --> 12:12.360
Elliot!

12:20.616 --> 12:21.696
Come on!

12:30.292 --> 12:31.292
(YELLING)

12:46.142 --> 12:47.142
Oh!

13:05.911 --> 13:07.411
Higher!

13:18.591 --> 13:20.511
(ELLIOT GRUNTING)

14:05.387 --> 14:07.557
(HOWLING)

14:07.640 --> 14:09.430
(HOWLING)

14:59.108 --> 15:00.188
What are you looking at?

15:00.985 --> 15:03.025
(MAKING GUTTURAL NOISES)

15:38.981 --> 15:40.151
This way?

15:40.316 --> 15:41.976
We're pretty far from home.

15:44.153 --> 15:45.153
(ELLIOT GRUNTING)

15:48.824 --> 15:50.204
(GRACE HUMMING)

16:31.116 --> 16:33.116
(OWL HOOTING)

16:34.411 --> 16:35.951
There you are.

17:20.749 --> 17:22.579
No one's gonna cut you down now.

17:37.641 --> 17:38.961
WENTWORTH:
You ready to go, Grace?

17:43.564 --> 17:44.654
Yeah.

17:54.116 --> 17:55.276
Just a second.

17:56.201 --> 17:57.871
Come on, Grace. Not again.

17:58.620 --> 18:00.330
GRACE: I'm just settling a score.

18:05.669 --> 18:07.249
One for Jack. One for you, huh?

18:07.629 --> 18:09.509
Yeah. Something like that.

18:09.590 --> 18:10.590
(WENTWORTH CHUCKLES)

18:10.674 --> 18:12.514
Aren't you two
supposed to be getting hitched?

18:12.676 --> 18:14.886
Yep! Just keeping him on his toes.

18:15.971 --> 18:17.221
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

18:45.834 --> 18:46.844
(SNIFFING)

19:03.602 --> 19:04.652
Look.

19:06.355 --> 19:07.355
(SNIFFING)

19:09.358 --> 19:10.568
(SNEEZES)

19:11.360 --> 19:12.820
Ew!

19:14.071 --> 19:15.201
Elliot!

20:00.284 --> 20:01.544
Pete and Elliot...

20:03.537 --> 20:04.957
are going...

20:05.122 --> 20:07.172
(VOCALIZING)

20:07.249 --> 20:08.249
And then...

20:08.458 --> 20:09.958
(CONTINUES VOCALIZING)

20:11.712 --> 20:14.672
Then they go down,
and down, and down!

20:19.720 --> 20:21.180
And then...

20:27.811 --> 20:28.811
Hmm.

20:29.229 --> 20:30.979
(MAKING GUTTURAL NOISES)

20:35.819 --> 20:38.159
I wonder where that lady came from.

20:38.864 --> 20:40.914
(MAKING GUTTURAL NOISES)

20:44.119 --> 20:45.829
Don't worry.

20:45.996 --> 20:47.706
I won't let her hurt you.

20:49.499 --> 20:50.499
(YAWNING)

20:53.003 --> 20:54.553
(YAWNING)

20:56.048 --> 20:57.668
(GRUNTING)

21:09.728 --> 21:11.018
Good night, Elliot.

21:30.165 --> 21:31.165
(ELLIOT SNORING)

21:37.923 --> 21:39.223
(DISTANT CRASHING)

21:39.299 --> 21:40.509
(GASPS)

21:40.592 --> 21:41.592
(ELLIOT GRUNTS)

21:46.014 --> 21:47.064
Elliot.

21:47.307 --> 21:48.307
(SNORING)

22:25.804 --> 22:27.184
MAN: Timber!

23:07.971 --> 23:09.391
MAN 1: Hey, Gavin.

23:10.223 --> 23:12.143
Did Jack give the okay to cut this deep?

23:12.809 --> 23:15.689
Don't worry about Jack.
Just keep cutting.

23:19.983 --> 23:21.743
GRACE: Who said it was
okay to be here?

23:21.902 --> 23:23.046
MAN 2: I just go where they tell me.

23:23.070 --> 23:24.360
GRACE: Where's Jack?

23:24.529 --> 23:25.699
MAN 2: There he is!

23:28.658 --> 23:29.948
This is so out of line, Jack.

23:30.118 --> 23:32.305
You're not supposed to be cutting
anywhere near this deep.

23:32.329 --> 23:33.389
I didn't know anything about this either.

23:33.413 --> 23:34.503
This wasn't my call, Grace.

23:34.664 --> 23:35.834
Then, whose was it?

23:39.002 --> 23:40.052
Of course.

23:40.212 --> 23:41.439
JACK: Let me handle this, please?

23:41.463 --> 23:43.303
GRACE: You don't handle it.
That's the problem.

23:43.423 --> 23:45.013
JACK: You're right, and Gavin is Gavin.

23:45.175 --> 23:47.135
He's my brother.

23:47.344 --> 23:49.184
Hey, I have to get to school.

23:50.055 --> 23:51.199
JACK: Could you wait
in the truck, sweetheart?

23:51.223 --> 23:52.223
We'll just be a minute.

23:53.892 --> 23:54.994
GRACE: Let's go through the maps.

23:55.018 --> 23:56.058
Let's review them.

24:29.761 --> 24:30.761
NATALIE: Hello?

24:41.690 --> 24:43.360
- (TWIG BREAKS)
- (GASPS)

24:45.026 --> 24:46.066
Wait!

25:00.750 --> 25:02.210
Where are you?

25:06.173 --> 25:07.173
Whoa!

25:07.340 --> 25:08.880
How'd you get up there?

25:21.646 --> 25:23.856
Come on! Slow down.

25:24.649 --> 25:25.729
You're pretty good at this.

25:39.164 --> 25:40.174
(SCREAMS)

25:41.791 --> 25:43.001
(NATALIE SCREAMING)

25:44.377 --> 25:45.417
Help!

25:48.673 --> 25:49.673
(BOTH SCREAMING)

25:50.800 --> 25:52.220
(SCREAMING AND GRUNTING)

25:56.264 --> 25:57.644
Don't let go!

25:58.475 --> 25:59.515
(GRUNTING)

25:59.643 --> 26:00.693
No! (SCREAMS)

26:00.810 --> 26:01.940
(CHUCKLING)

26:02.562 --> 26:03.562
(PANTING)

26:08.610 --> 26:09.610
Don't!

26:10.862 --> 26:12.032
I'm hurt!

26:27.170 --> 26:28.550
How old are you?

26:30.131 --> 26:31.131
Five?

26:31.841 --> 26:34.341
You're pretty big to be a five-year-old.

26:38.306 --> 26:39.636
What's your name?

26:40.225 --> 26:41.225
Pete.

26:41.810 --> 26:42.810
Pete.

26:44.896 --> 26:46.686
You look like a Pete.

26:46.856 --> 26:48.296
- My name's Natalie.
- JACK: Natalie!

26:49.693 --> 26:51.493
NATALIE: Daddy!
JACK: Natalie!

26:51.653 --> 26:52.653
Daddy!

26:52.821 --> 26:54.548
What were you thinking?
You can't run away like that.

26:54.572 --> 26:55.662
What happened to you?

26:56.032 --> 26:57.242
I fell out of a tree.

26:57.409 --> 26:58.739
You fell out of a tree?

26:58.910 --> 27:00.110
What were you doing in a tree?

27:00.954 --> 27:02.124
Following him.

27:07.752 --> 27:08.752
Oh.

27:09.796 --> 27:11.046
NATALIE: His name is Pete.

27:13.216 --> 27:14.626
Hey.

27:15.093 --> 27:18.313
Pete? Is that your name?

27:19.347 --> 27:20.517
Pete?

27:20.682 --> 27:21.812
Wait, wait, wait!

27:26.479 --> 27:27.859
Where'd you come from?

27:28.481 --> 27:29.651
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

27:31.192 --> 27:33.612
Do you know where your parents are?

27:33.778 --> 27:34.898
Your family?

27:41.369 --> 27:42.369
Hey.

27:45.040 --> 27:46.620
Where'd you get that?

27:47.542 --> 27:48.592
Wait!

27:48.668 --> 27:49.748
PETE: Elliot!
GRACE: Pete!

27:52.213 --> 27:53.513
Whoa, there, little buddy.

27:53.673 --> 27:55.013
Where are you going so...

27:56.801 --> 27:58.601
Hey, kid! Come back here.

28:01.848 --> 28:02.848
Come on, kid!

28:03.641 --> 28:04.771
Careful, Gavin!

28:13.735 --> 28:14.735
(YAWNS)

28:23.119 --> 28:24.119
(SNIFFING)

28:38.051 --> 28:39.051
(SNIFFS)

28:40.845 --> 28:41.845
(GRUNTS)

28:46.768 --> 28:48.648
(CALLING OUT)

28:48.728 --> 28:49.728
JACK: Doesn't matter.

28:49.896 --> 28:51.332
The sheriff, the rangers, everybody else

28:51.356 --> 28:52.541
are gonna be locking this site down...

28:52.565 --> 28:54.975
until they figure out
where that kid came from.

28:55.151 --> 28:56.401
Hey, you hear that?

28:56.569 --> 28:58.239
Don't change the subject, Gavin.

29:12.043 --> 29:13.521
GAVIN: Every time I try
and take some initiative...

29:13.545 --> 29:15.085
you shut me down.

29:17.590 --> 29:19.070
If we hadn't been cutting out here...

29:19.134 --> 29:21.344
we never would've found
that kid in the first place.

29:21.511 --> 29:23.261
We're doing good work here, Jack.

29:23.430 --> 29:24.698
And we need a big score
to help us compete.

29:24.722 --> 29:25.866
What about a few years from now...

29:25.890 --> 29:27.243
when we have nothing left to cut down

29:27.267 --> 29:28.587
because you keep jumping the gun?

29:29.394 --> 29:31.038
- Where are you going?
- Where do you think?

29:31.062 --> 29:32.112
(ENGINE STARTS)

29:32.188 --> 29:34.318
You're not the only family
I gotta worry about.

29:38.278 --> 29:40.318
Let me know how Pete's doing, will ya?

29:40.822 --> 29:41.822
(GRUNTS SOFTLY)

29:49.247 --> 29:51.617
What's wrong, Gavin?
Jack giving you a hard time?

29:52.459 --> 29:53.919
Oh, you know Jack.

29:54.085 --> 29:56.545
He's just sore because
his girlfriend's stepping on his toes.

29:57.213 --> 29:58.633
WOODROW: Redheads, man.

30:02.844 --> 30:04.304
GAVIN: Look out!
MAN: Look out!

30:14.981 --> 30:16.151
MAN: What was that?

30:16.441 --> 30:17.441
(GUN COCKS)

30:21.654 --> 30:22.864
Let's go hunting.

30:28.203 --> 30:29.203
WOMAN: Pete.

30:33.374 --> 30:35.424
Time to wake up, Pete.

30:38.296 --> 30:39.456
Momma?

30:43.968 --> 30:45.928
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENTS
ON PA)

30:48.473 --> 30:49.773
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

30:52.393 --> 30:53.393
Elliot?

31:15.208 --> 31:16.208
(GASPS)

31:18.378 --> 31:19.378
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

31:23.424 --> 31:24.704
SHERIFF DENTLER: How's he doing?

31:24.801 --> 31:27.431
DR. MARQUEZ: Pretty well,
all things considered.

31:27.595 --> 31:30.175
No signs of malnourishment
or serious exposure.

31:30.348 --> 31:31.948
He might have a bump to the head, but...

31:31.975 --> 31:34.265
- Lucky kid.
- Super lucky.

31:34.435 --> 31:35.765
How'd he get out there?

31:35.937 --> 31:37.977
My guess, he was
on a picnic or a camping trip.

31:38.147 --> 31:39.416
He wandered off from his family,

31:39.440 --> 31:40.480
got himself lost.

31:40.650 --> 31:42.490
Sure, but when?

31:42.652 --> 31:44.742
It looks like he's been out there

31:44.821 --> 31:47.161
for who knows how long.

31:47.323 --> 31:48.583
And he had this.

31:48.741 --> 31:49.911
You sure that's yours?

31:52.996 --> 31:54.076
Pretty sure.

31:54.247 --> 31:55.787
Here we are. All fixed up.

31:55.957 --> 31:58.167
Hey, there. How you feeling?

31:58.334 --> 32:01.344
It was just a scrape. Where's Pete?

32:02.463 --> 32:04.053
I'm gonna take Natalie home,

32:04.132 --> 32:06.342
then head back out to the forest.

32:06.509 --> 32:08.969
Maybe there's something out there...

32:09.137 --> 32:12.137
some clue, or something.

32:12.307 --> 32:13.847
Could you call me when he wakes up?

32:14.017 --> 32:15.437
DR. MARQUEZ: Of course.

32:15.602 --> 32:16.892
When he wakes up,

32:16.978 --> 32:18.978
I think it would be best
to take things slowly.

32:19.147 --> 32:21.607
One step at a time.
Let him know he's safe.

32:22.442 --> 32:24.112
We don't know what he's been through.

32:24.277 --> 32:26.697
SHERIFF DENTLER:
We put in a call in to Social Services.

32:26.779 --> 32:28.869
They'll know exactly how to handle this.

32:29.032 --> 32:31.952
For the time being,
he'll be just fine right here.

