in the forest more than anything.

39:18.399 --> 39:20.109
I loved being out there.

39:20.276 --> 39:22.696
It was so fun with the squirrels

39:22.778 --> 39:25.358
and the birds and the trees.

39:26.907 --> 39:28.617
So, when I grew up...

39:28.784 --> 39:31.254
I made it my job to protect the woods

39:31.370 --> 39:33.250
and everything in them.

39:34.623 --> 39:38.093
Which I suppose includes you.

39:38.919 --> 39:39.919
(CHUCKLES)

39:41.130 --> 39:42.420
And Elliot?

39:43.549 --> 39:44.759
Who's Elliot?

39:46.594 --> 39:47.894
JACK: Grace?

39:56.771 --> 39:57.956
JACK: Are you sure about this?

39:57.980 --> 40:00.320
It's just until
we found out where he belongs.

40:01.650 --> 40:02.650
Who knows?

40:02.777 --> 40:06.567
Maybe being around someone
his own age will help him open up.

40:06.739 --> 40:08.569
Maybe he'll tell us where he came from.

40:08.741 --> 40:10.951
You don't touch it. You eat it.

40:11.118 --> 40:12.288
Like this.

40:13.996 --> 40:15.076
JACK: I gotta admit...

40:15.247 --> 40:18.167
living out in the woods,
doing things his own way...

40:19.460 --> 40:21.460
sounds like a boy after your own heart.

40:29.512 --> 40:31.182
ABNER: I think we're lost.

40:31.347 --> 40:33.427
BOBBY: Ah, Gavin knows
what he's doing.

40:34.183 --> 40:36.313
WOODROW: You said
that three miles ago.

40:36.811 --> 40:38.691
BOBBY: The river's
up around that bend.

40:39.480 --> 40:40.480
We can just follow that,

40:40.523 --> 40:41.750
